Only 12% of the patients had high renin profiles. These low renin people are at a low risk of heart attack, Dr. On the other hand, in other patients with high blood pressure, the activity of the renin is much lower than is warranted by the degree of salt in the blood. Such high renin people are at a high risk of a heart attack. The Cornell cardiologist has argued that in many people with high blood pressure the activity of the renin in the blood is much higher than is warranted by the amount of salt in the blood. 